decks.notes: This deck focuses on playing aggressively with efficient creatures and burn spells to quickly overwhelm the opponent. The inclusion of Jegantha as a companion allows for additional value and flexibility. The mana base is built to support the diverse color requirements of the deck, enabling the player to consistently cast their spells. The Leyline cards provide additional support and protection for the creatures, while Tribal Flames adds extra reach to close out games. Overall, the deck aims to apply pressure early and maintain a constant threat presence to secure victories.

The deck aims to utilize the combination of Emry, Lurker of the Loch and Underworld Breach to repeatedly cast powerful spells from the graveyard, fueling a steady stream of card advantage and mana acceleration. Mishra's Bauble, Mox Amber, and Urza's Saga generate additional value while Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student helps dig for combo pieces. The goal is to assemble the combo quickly to overwhelm opponents with powerful spells like Thassa's Oracle or Malevolent Rumble, ultimately achieving victory through a combination of card advantage and overwhelming board presence.

This deck revolves around assembling multiple combo pieces to generate a powerful win condition. The deck includes cards that provide ramp, protection, and card draw, all working together to set up a game-winning combo. The goal is to use the various pieces in combination to create a powerful board state that overwhelms the opponent and secures victory. The deck's synergy and combo potential make it a formidable force in Modern 1 vs 1 games.

This Eldrazi Aggro deck focuses on overwhelming the opponent with powerful Eldrazi creatures while disrupting their game plan with cards like Thought-Knot Seer and All Is Dust. Chalice of the Void is used to control the opponent's spells, while Kozilek's Command provides versatility and removal. By utilizing aggressive creatures like Eldrazi Obligator and It That Heralds the End, the deck aims to quickly close out the game. The land base includes Eldrazi Temple and Cavern of Souls to help cast Eldrazi spells efficiently, while also providing some utility with Prismatic Vista and Ramunap Ruins.

The deck focuses on assembling a combo involving Heliod, Sun-Crowned and Spike Feeder to create an infinite life gain and creature pump engine. Auriok Champion provides protection and synergy with the combo pieces, while Collected Company helps to find key creatures quickly. The deck also includes mana acceleration with Arbor Elf, Utopia Sprawl, and ramp lands to power out its threats. Rosie Cotton of South Lane and Guide of Souls provide additional support and card advantage. The goal is to quickly set up the combo and overwhelm the opponent with a massive life total and powerful creatures.

The deck aims to create a powerful combo using Heliod, Sun-Crowned and Spike Feeder to gain infinite life and create an infinitely large Walking Ballista to deal lethal damage to the opponent. The deck focuses on ramping with Arbor Elf and Utopia Sprawl to quickly assemble the combo pieces and protect the combo with Ranger-Captain of Eos. Collected Company and Kayla's Reconstruction provide additional ways to find combo pieces while maintaining board presence. Overall, the deck is designed to quickly assemble a game-winning combo while maintaining flexibility and resilience against disruption.

The deck revolves around the combo of discarding creatures with cycling abilities, then casting Living End to bring them all back from the graveyard onto the battlefield. The deck includes a mix of creatures with cycling abilities to enable the combo as well as counterspells and protection spells to disrupt opponents' strategies. It aims to quickly fill up the graveyard with cycling creatures and then cast Living End to overwhelm the opponent with a board full of powerful creatures. The deck also includes some control elements to help survive long enough to execute the combo.

The main concept of this Merfolk aggro deck is to overwhelm the opponent with a fast and efficient creature strategy. By utilizing lords like Lord of Atlantis and Master of the Pearl Trident, alongside disruptive creatures like Merfolk Trickster, the deck aims to boost its creatures and control the board. Cards like Aether Vial and Force of Negation provide additional versatility and protection. The deck focuses on maintaining a strong board presence and tempo, utilizing its synergy to outpace and outmaneuver the opponent for a quick victory.

This Mono Black Control deck focuses on controlling the board by using removal spells like Fatal Push and Fell the Profane, while also disrupting the opponent's hand with cards like Thoughtseize and Inquisition of Kozilek. The key strategy is to stall the game until you can play powerful threats like Sheoldred, the Apocalypse and The One Ring. The deck also utilizes graveyard recursion with Necrodominance and Boggart Trawler. The inclusion of cards like Soul Spike and The Meathook Massacre provides alternate win conditions to ensure victory.

The deck focuses on utilizing the UrzaTron lands to quickly ramp up mana and cast powerful Eldrazi creatures and spells to control the game. The deck features removal spells like Dismember and All Is Dust to handle threats, while also using cards like Thought-Knot Seer and Karn, the Great Creator to disrupt the opponent's game plan. The inclusion of cards like Ugin, the Spirit Dragon and World Breaker provide additional board control options. The deck aims to establish a dominant board presence and overwhelm the opponent with its powerful creatures and spells.
